Class World

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.geometry.SpatialObject
      • com.kuka.geometry.World
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    ICapabilityContainer

    public final class World
extends SpatialObject
    Spatial object representing World.

    Some operations defined in SpatialObject are not applicable to World object, therefore an UnsupportedOperationException is thrown when trying to use them.

      • setTransient

        public void setTransient(boolean isTransient)
        Description copied from class: SpatialObject
        Set the 'transient' property of this object by making it either transient or non-transient.

        Transient objects have a weak connection to the scene graph. This means that they can be removed by a clean up function. Compared to that, non-transient objects have a stronger connection to the scene graph which means that they will not be removed by a clean up.
        Use SpatialObject.isTransient() to request the current state of the property.

        Overrides:
        setTransient in class SpatialObject
        Parameters:
        isTransient - the new value of this property

      • setTransientRecursive

        public void setTransientRecursive(boolean isTransient)
        Description copied from class: SpatialObject
        Set the 'transient' property of this object and of all children (recursively) by making them either transient or non-transient.

        Transient objects have a weak connection to the scene graph. This means that they can be removed by a clean up function. Compared to that, non-transient objects have a stronger connection to the scene graph which means that they will not be removed by a clean up.
        Use SpatialObject.isTransient() to request the current state of the property.

        Overrides:
        setTransientRecursive in class SpatialObject
        Parameters:
        isTransient - the new value of this property

      • fireValidationEvent

        protected void fireValidationEvent(TreeEvent event)
        Description copied from class: SpatialObject
        Fires a validation event. Validation events are fired before a change is made. The event is forwarded to the parent by default.
        CAUTION: Always make sure you own the spatial object tree lock when you call the default implementation!
        Overrides:
        fireValidationEvent in class SpatialObject
        Parameters:
        event - the TreeEvent that contains information about an upcoming change.
